#### The situation

We are using custom SpriteBatch effects in our game. For example:

```
sampler TextureSampler : register(s0);
uniform float2 Offset = float2(0, 0);

float4 main(float4 position : SV_Position, float4 color : COLOR0, float2 texCoord : TEXCOORD0) : COLOR0
{
    return tex2D(TextureSampler, texCoord + Offset);
}

technique Displacement
{
    pass Pass1
    {
#if HLSL
        PixelShader = compile ps_4_0_level_9_3 main();
#else
        PixelShader = compile ps_2_0 main();
#endif
    }
}
```
#### The exception

"No vertex shader attached."
https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/blob/develop/MonoGame.Framework/Graphics/Shader/ShaderProgramCache.cs#L138

It happenes **rarely** and **only on Android devices** (WP8, W8, iOS are fine).

> Hi, it happenned only once, and I never had this problem again.

Do we need to directly specify a pass through vertex shader? Any idea?
